text: Lu Suyan (born 29 May 1965) is a Chinese former cyclist. She competed at the 1984 Summer Olympics and the 1988 Summer Olympics and 1990 Asian Games. ==References== Category:1965 births Category:Living people Category:Chinese female cyclists Category:Olympic cyclists of China Category:Cyclists at the 1984 Summer Olympics Category:Cyclists at the 1988 Summer Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Asian Games medalists in cycling Category:Cyclists at the 1990 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 1990 Asian Games Category:Asian Games gold medalists for China
